speech.p:
asked the Prime Minister (1) whether it is intended in the near future to take powers to control the location of industry in the manner suggested in Cmd. 5303, or in any other manner;

(2) whether his attention has been called to the suggestion made in Cmd. 5303 that,

whereas agriculture has in recent years been accorded preferential treatment in a lavish manner, the Special Areas have received no comparable preferential treatment; whether he accepts the comparison as just; and, if so, what immediate action he will take to redress the balance;

(3) whether it is intended to propose further preferential treatment for new industries located in the Special Areas in the manner suggested in Cmd. 5303, or in any other manner?
